				<div id="post-1583" class="post-1583 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-chip-tunes category-music category-platform-game category-technical tag-chip-tune tag-music-2 tag-tracker tag-tutorial">
					<h1 class="entry-title">Composing in-game music &#8211; retro style</h1>

					<div class="entry-meta">
						<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/2012/05/15/composing-in-game-music/" title="2:01 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">May 15, 2012</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/author/paulfirth/" title="View all posts by Paul Firth">Paul Firth</a></span>					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

					<div class="entry-content">
						<img width="150" height="120" src="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/figure3-150x120.png" class="attachment-single-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="(Screenshot of Sound Tracker from http://hardcoregaming101.net)" />						
				<!-- Social Sharing Toolkit v2.0.4 | http://www.marijnrongen.com/wordpress-plugins/social_sharing_toolkit/ -->
				<div class="mr_social_sharing_wrapper"><span class="mr_social_sharing"><script type="text/javascript">
