		<div class="comment-body"><p>Thanks Ren�, that was an interesting article. For our last game (<a href="http://www.volumesoffun.com/voxeliens/" rel="nofollow">Voxeliens</a>) I did almost all of the programming and art myself, but music was the one area where I simply wouldn&#8217;t have known where to start. In the end I just found some royalty-free chiptune music and used that. I&#8217;m still not sure I&#8217;d actually attempt the process myself but it&#8217;s useful to know what goes into it.</p>
<p>Do you have any other samples of your work? We&#8217;ve not actually got a project at the moment, but we expect to work on another 3D retro-style game in the future and it&#8217;s always worth knowing people with relevant skills. Especially local people as I also live in Groningen <img src="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" />  Sorry I don&#8217;t speak Dutch though&#8230;</p>
