		<div class="comment-body"><p>Hey guys!</p>
<p>A blatant pitch since I&#8217;d like to think I&#8217;m part of the fore-mentioned dying breed <img src="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" />  If you need more music in old-school format I&#8217;m absolutely available!</p>
<p>My portfolio is under heavy reconstruction, unfortunately&#8230; but here&#8217;s my latest C64-chiptune: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k7qEOAgvBX0" rel="nofollow">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k7qEOAgvBX0</a></p>
<p>I can do practically anything from modules of different flavour (.mod, .s3m, .xm, .it etc) to even native chip format of various 8-bit machines. Can practically emulate any machine with distinctive sound: NES, SNES, C64, Amiga, Adlib, Megadrive/Genesis etc.</p>
<p>I decided to go on my own way after working for others for too long in game biz and hopefully someone needs my services <img src="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
<p>Cheers!</p>
</div>

